  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a tagine or heavy‑bottomed pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the diced bacon and cook until it starts to crisp, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, and ginger; sauté until the onion is translucent, about 3 minutes.",
    "Stir in the cumin, coriander, smoked paprika, and cinnamon, cooking for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Add the carrots, sweet potato, raisins, preserved lemon strips, and olives, tossing to coat with spices.",
    "Pour in the broth, bring to a gentle boil, then reduce heat to low and cover. Simmer for 25–30 minutes, until vegetables are tender.",
    "Stir in the tomato paste, season with salt and pepper, and simmer uncovered for an additional 5 minutes to thicken the sauce.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a serving dish and dot the top with crumbled feta cheese.",
    "Cover the dish with foil and let the residual heat melt the cheese into a gooey, golden topping, about 5 minutes.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with fresh cilantro or parsley if desired. Enjoy!"
  ],
